    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">The Duke de Soulé</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Harvey</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Foreign Affairs,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 29, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In addition to the notes I addressed you on the 23d and 26th instant, I have now
                    the honor to inform you that on the 26th instant the Portuguese steamer-of-war
                    Mindello left this port bound for the Azores, in order to superintend the
                    execution of the orders transmitted to the respective authorities regarding the
                    punctual compliance with the decree of July 29, 1864.</p>
                <p>I renew, on this occasion, the assurances of my distinguished consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>DUKE DE SOULÉ.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                        >c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
